com.shc.ahttp.client.request

Class AHttpGetRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.shc.ahttp.client.request.ABasicAuthHttpRequestBase
      • com.shc.ahttp.client.request.AHttpGetRequest

  • public class AHttpGetRequest
extends ABasicAuthHttpRequestBase
    The Apache HttpGetRequest class facilitates doing a get request to given url and supports Basic Authentication.

    Simple usage : 
     String url = "https://httpbin.org/image/jpeg";
 String username = "username";
 String password = "password";
 AHttpGetClient aHttpGetClient = new AHttpGetClient();
 System.out.println(aHttpGetClient.executeGet(url, username, password));


    The class also provides overloaded methods to specify additional options such as :
    • Custom Headers
    • Custom Encoding
    • Option to include response header in the returned response object
    • Specify connect timeout
    • Options to send request without basic authentications
    Version:
